name: CET Teleport
overview: CET Teleport is one of Europe’s major teleports and was built by Deutsche Telekom in 1987 for satellite broadcast and VSAT services. The Teleport is located in northwest Germany giving it a commanding view of the skies with visibility from the Eastern Pacific, West Coast USA, South America, then covering Europe and Africa, all the way across Russia and China, and all of Asia, down to Australia. The Teleport is host to over 50 antennas from 15m downwards operating in C, Ku, Ka, K and X bands and is fully integrated into Deutshe Telekom’s German fibre network, providing it with access to the terrestrial network for Internet connectivity and data voice backhaul.
